author: Bob Condotta
title: Seattle Seahawks coach Pete Carroll says there’s nothing to USC rumors
text:
Seattle Seahawks coach Pete Carroll says there’s nothing to USC rumors Originally published October 19, 2015 at 5:26 pm Seattle Seahawks coach Pete Carroll says he's flattered by rumors that USC would be interested in having him return but that he has no plans to leave his current job. 
Rumors that some at USC might have Seattle coach Pete Carroll on the shortlist of possible new coaches there grew on Monday after Dan Patrick mentioned it earlier in the day. 
Carroll said during his regular Monday press conference, though, that he has no plans of returning to the school where he coached from 2001-09. 
“I would say this —I love USC,” he said. “It’s a great place. Flattered. I appreciate it Dan. But that’s not happening. We’re in good shape here.” 
Carroll,who turned 64 last month, has a contract with the Seahawks through the 2016 season reported to pay him more than $7 million a season. Most Read Stories
